    <ul>
      <li>Have 1-2 students share the method, including any expressions or equations they used to solve the first problem.</li>
      <li>Have 2-3 students share the expressions or equations they used to solve the last problem.</li>
      <li>
        <q>¿En qué se parecen estos métodos? ¿En qué son diferentes?</q>  (Some people added the maple and oak trees together and then subtracted it from the number of fir trees. Some people subtracted the number of maple trees from fir trees and then subtracted the number of oak trees. Each way found the same number of trees.)
      </li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>


